[Cyclospora is usually transmitted to humans by berries contaminated with human waste used as fertilizer. In some previous outbreaks it has been linked to imported berries, but this can not be assumed before a case control study has been performed. The infection is usually self limiting in immunocompetent individuals. - Mod. EP

The state of Texas can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2638219,245. Dallas Tarrant, and Collin counties in north east Texas can be seen on the map at http://geology.com/county-map/texas-county-map.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
